"NOT FOUND"|"p. 10. 6 turmas] ***troops of cavalry***. To each legion was attached a body of 300 cavalry divided into 10 turmae ; each turma had a vexillum of its own and was commanded by three officers called decuriones and three of lower grade called optiones. Kraner remarks that Caesar does not use the word turma to denote a body of cavalry without some explanatory word such as equitum."

