"cum fama exercitus ad hostes esset perlata, calamitate ceterorum ducti carnutes desertis VICIS OPPIDISQUE, quae tolerandae hiemis causa constitutis repente exiguis ad necessitatem aedificiis incolebant (nuper enim devicti complura oppida dimiserant), dispersi profugiunt."|"vicis oppidisque] ***villages and strongholds***: the Gallic oppidum was a large entrenchment for which a naturally strong site was usually selected."

