"NOT FOUND"|"18 nunquam profecto esset inlaturus] ***he would surely never feel disposed to inflict at all ***. The barbarians say that they had been utterly ruined in the contest; had it been in Caesar***s power to inflict this ruin on them without a battle and while their power was unimpaired (integris), he would have been far too generous to do it; let him then be content with the disasters they had suffered in war and not add to their sufferings."

