"ita, cum palude impedita a castris castra dividi videret, quae transeundi difficultas celeritatem insequendi tardare posset, atque id iugum quod trans paludem paene ad hostium castra pertineret mediocri valle a CASTRIS EOrum intercisum animum adverteret, pontibus palude constrata legiones traducit celeriterque in summam planitiem iugi pervenit, quae declivi fastigio duobus ab lateribus muniebatur."|"castris eo loco metatis] metari castra is to measure out the ground for a camp, to pitch a camp, eo loco on the extremity of the ridge of M Collet or ***on the heights that lie immediately to the right of the Ru du Berne*** (Kampen). Notice the unpleasant repetition of castra after castris, which might easily have been avoided."

