"NOT FOUND"|"celeriter] celeritas was conspicuous in all that Caesar did. It isworthy of note that the adverb celeriter occurs about 80 times in the 7 books of the Gallic War."

"NOT FOUND"|"flumeti] if the Puy d***lssolu be really the site of Uxellodunum the word flumen must be applied vaguely to four streams, the Sourdoie, Dordogne, Tourmente and a little brook running into the last named, the four forming a circuit round the hill complete save for an interval of one Roman mile where the ground is rugged with a deep cross valley running through it. Kampen remarks that the case is simplified if the Sourdoie originally emptied itself into the Tourmente, which the configuration of the ground shows to have been possible."

"NOT FOUND"|"Chap. 50."

"NOT FOUND"|"bellum Parthicum\ it was in 65 that difficulties first arose between the Romans and the Parthians, but war was not declared till 56. Crassus went out as commander in chief in 54, his defeat and death took place in June of the following year ; his place was taken temporarily by Gaius Cassius Longinus till the appointment of M. Bibulus as Governor of Syria andr M. Tullius Cicero of Cilicia in March 51. Unfavourable news arrived from Bibulus in May 59 and next month it was decreed that two legions should be sent out under L. Marius."

